snippet.textDisplay: The moment my chest suddenly tightened and I choked back tears, I knew this song brought back memories of a very difficult phase during my PhD. studies abroad. Nothing was working for me, and time was not on my side either. I was at the peak of my low. I remember going to an empty home, sitting on the bed, and just letting the tears flow. I didn't want to burden my mom with my problems and so just crying alone was the only option in a foreign land. Mothers are irreplaceable, but this song holds that warm hug and comfort that mums give to us. The reassurance and the strength to battle again and relentlessly. That part of my life is over, but the memories remain. Kudos to the entire team for this song. It definitely is that warm hug on a down day. Thank you. ❤❤❤

snippet.textDisplay:
Dear SG,  
There are times in life when we really need something to keep us going. Lately, things have been hard, and during those moments, your music has always given me strength. I find it difficult to put into words just how much that means to me.  

As I write this, I'm tearing up because you've been my constant support, my rock. Your songs feel like a warm hug, giving me comfort when I need it the most. Even on the toughest days, they make things a little easier, as if each note is telling me everything will be okay.  

Thank you for being that light, even from a distance. I may not have the right words, but I hope you know how much your music and presence mean to me. You’ve been with me through all the highs and lows, and for that, I’m forever grateful. I hope one day I can fully express how much love and gratitude I have for you.
